      "description": "source -  - Select the source operator type for the laser image.\n\n sop - Use a  as the source for the Laser image. Appart from position attributes, the 's point color attributes are used to determine the color output. chop - Use a  as the source for the Laser image. The  expects x and y channels and every sample will be interpreted as a point to be drawn. To draw multiple shapes, also specify an id named channel to identify each shape. All other channels will be interpreted as color channels and blanking will be applied to those. This makes it possible to drive Lasers that have more than just rgb diodes active.",
